1
00:00:11,700 --> 00:00:12,967
Who are they, Ando?

2
00:00:13,033 --> 00:00:14,533
I think they're thieves.

3
00:00:14,600 --> 00:00:15,733
Hello, Ma'am Olive.

4
00:00:15,800 --> 00:00:19,233
Mookie's in Immaculate Heart
Pediatric Hospital.

5
00:00:19,300 --> 00:00:20,133
Are you sure?
Yes.

6
00:00:21,133 --> 00:00:22,167
It was only right
to give them away

7
00:00:22,233 --> 00:00:24,500
because I wasn't a good mother.

8
00:00:24,567 --> 00:00:26,400
Emma wouldn't be a good person

9
00:00:26,467 --> 00:00:28,400
if you weren't
a good mother to her.

10
00:00:28,467 --> 00:00:29,467
Mookie?

11
00:00:29,533 --> 00:00:30,433
Mommy?

12
00:00:30,500 --> 00:00:32,200
Didn't I already
explain everything

13
00:00:32,267 --> 00:00:33,700
that Doc Charles said?

14
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:36,767
I will do everything you want
once I see the proof

15
00:00:36,833 --> 00:00:39,467
that I'm really sick.

16
00:00:39,533 --> 00:00:42,600
Let's both pray we reunite
with our children.

17
00:00:42,667 --> 00:00:44,500
Once your test results
comes out,

18
00:00:44,567 --> 00:00:49,467
you will realize that everything
I do is for your protection.

19
00:01:24,167 --> 00:01:24,767
Okay.

20
00:01:25,833 --> 00:01:26,500
I'm leaving, Flor.
Take charge.

21
00:01:27,500 --> 00:01:28,833
Yes, Ma'am. Be safe.

22
00:01:37,100 --> 00:01:38,233
I knew it. You're thieves.

23
00:01:38,300 --> 00:01:39,700
- No. You're mistaken.
- No.

24
00:01:39,767 --> 00:01:40,467
What do you mean by no?
Hey.

25
00:01:41,167 --> 00:01:42,033
Mister, wait.

26
00:01:42,100 --> 00:01:43,233
Mister!

27
00:01:43,300 --> 00:01:43,700
Dan!

28
00:01:44,467 --> 00:01:45,567
Stop!

29
00:01:45,633 --> 00:01:46,400
Please stop!
That's enough!

30
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:49,233
- Leave!
- We're not thieves.

31
00:01:49,300 --> 00:01:51,800
The real thief is the one
living in that house!

32
00:01:51,867 --> 00:01:53,167
She took our child!

33
00:01:53,233 --> 00:01:54,867
What are you talking about?

34
00:01:54,933 --> 00:01:56,367
You better leave.

35
00:01:56,433 --> 00:01:59,433
We're not going anywhere
until we get answers.

36
00:02:00,267 --> 00:02:01,100
Are you not leaving?

37
00:02:02,033 --> 00:02:02,933
- Wait, wait, Mister!
- Get out of here!

38
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:04,133
- Don't! Don't!
- Wait!

39
00:02:08,033 --> 00:02:08,867
Are you leaving or not?

40
00:02:10,067 --> 00:02:11,467
We're leaving.

41
00:02:13,067 --> 00:02:13,733
Go!

42
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:15,400
Let's go, Emma.

43
00:02:26,967 --> 00:02:27,833
Hello, Zayn?

44
00:02:32,167 --> 00:02:32,867
Yes.

45
00:02:34,267 --> 00:02:36,433
She didn't scold me.

46
00:02:36,500 --> 00:02:37,267
Good to hear that.

47
00:02:38,067 --> 00:02:39,767
She was so upset yesterday.

48
00:02:39,833 --> 00:02:41,967
She's giving me the side eye.

49
00:02:42,033 --> 00:02:43,600
I actually find it weird.

50
00:02:44,567 --> 00:02:45,633
Something feels off.

51
00:02:46,567 --> 00:02:48,200
What do you mean?

52
00:02:48,300 --> 00:02:51,100
She let me get tested.

53
00:02:51,733 --> 00:02:53,500
And she didn't scold me.

54
00:02:54,167 --> 00:02:57,300
I thought she would lock me up
in the dark room,

55
00:02:57,367 --> 00:02:59,467
but she didn't.

56
00:03:00,233 --> 00:03:01,800
She was so nice to me.

57
00:03:01,867 --> 00:03:03,433
Why don't you seem happy?

58
00:03:04,133 --> 00:03:05,867
Because it feels off.

59
00:03:06,833 --> 00:03:09,800
I'm not sure if I'm only
being paranoid.

60
00:03:09,867 --> 00:03:14,600
But I'm sure she'll punish me
if I do something wrong.

61
00:03:15,167 --> 00:03:17,800
Well, just give her a chance.

62
00:03:17,867 --> 00:03:20,633
Maybe what happened was
a wake-up call to her.

63
00:03:21,467 --> 00:03:25,333
By the way, who told her
we were in the hospital?

64
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:27,267
Was it Flor?

65
00:03:27,333 --> 00:03:28,633
I'm sure it wasn't her.

66
00:03:29,067 --> 00:03:30,900
I know Flor.

67
00:03:30,967 --> 00:03:32,033
She's on my side.

68
00:03:33,967 --> 00:03:37,067
It doesn't matter anymore.

69
00:03:37,867 --> 00:03:40,800
What matters
is the test results.

70
00:03:41,933 --> 00:03:43,933
I really hope
I'm not sick, Zayn.

71
00:03:45,133 --> 00:03:46,233
I hope so, too, Mooks.

72
00:04:02,267 --> 00:04:02,833
Oh!
Miss!

73
00:04:03,833 --> 00:04:05,033
Your receipt.

74
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:10,867
Thank you.

75
00:04:29,633 --> 00:04:30,467
Danilo!

76
00:04:31,633 --> 00:04:32,600
Danilo!

77
00:04:33,533 --> 00:04:34,567
Hey, Miss.

78
00:04:34,633 --> 00:04:35,800
Where are you taking Kayla?

79
00:04:37,433 --> 00:04:38,067
Danilo!

80
00:04:38,533 --> 00:04:39,200
Danilo!

81
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:49,667
I wonder who that woman is.

82
00:04:50,467 --> 00:04:52,067
Is she Danilo's relative?

83
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:57,800
Why isn't he picking up?

84
00:04:58,633 --> 00:04:59,300
Danilo!

85
00:04:59,933 --> 00:05:00,800
Answer the call!

86
00:05:08,533 --> 00:05:09,500
Hello, Bukoy.

87
00:05:09,567 --> 00:05:10,800
Hello, Danilo.

88
00:05:10,867 --> 00:05:13,700
The woman who took your child
isn't in the province.

89
00:05:13,767 --> 00:05:14,833
I saw her in Manila.

90
00:05:14,900 --> 00:05:16,033
She's here.

91
00:05:16,100 --> 00:05:16,867
- What?
- What?

92
00:05:22,033 --> 00:05:22,900
Follow her, Bukoy!
Follow her!

93
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:25,567
Yes, I'm following her.

94
00:05:43,733 --> 00:05:45,867
What's taking our friend
so long?

95
00:05:45,933 --> 00:05:48,500
It seems like she's prayed
for the whole country.

96
00:05:49,533 --> 00:05:50,467
Relax.

97
00:05:50,967 --> 00:05:52,367
I'm almost done.

98
00:06:02,433 --> 00:06:03,200
Amen.

99
00:06:04,467 --> 00:06:05,433
Thank you.

100
00:06:06,967 --> 00:06:07,600
Let's go.

101
00:06:08,433 --> 00:06:09,833
We can go to the tournament.

102
00:06:09,900 --> 00:06:10,967
Wait.

103
00:06:11,033 --> 00:06:12,967
Why is your prayer so long?

104
00:06:14,433 --> 00:06:16,067
I pray harder because

105
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:20,533
Emma and Danilo
found out something

106
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:23,200
about my granddaughter's
kidnapper.

107
00:06:24,233 --> 00:06:24,967
Really?

108
00:06:25,667 --> 00:06:27,400
Let's pray some more.

109
00:06:27,467 --> 00:06:28,700
So that God will
get tired of us

110
00:06:28,767 --> 00:06:30,200
and give Emma
what she's asking for.

111
00:06:30,267 --> 00:06:31,533
- That's right.
- Come on.

112
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:32,633
Let's kneel.

113
00:06:38,700 --> 00:06:40,233
Don't let her get
out of your sight.

114
00:06:41,300 --> 00:06:43,000
Look where you're going!

115
00:06:43,067 --> 00:06:43,967
Sorry, Sir.

116
00:06:46,867 --> 00:06:47,267
Oh, no.

117
00:06:47,333 --> 00:06:48,400
Hello, Danilo?

118
00:06:49,900 --> 00:06:50,967
Bukoy, find her.

119
00:06:51,033 --> 00:06:52,233
Catch her.

120
00:06:54,300 --> 00:06:56,400
Okay, I'll follow her.

121
00:06:56,467 --> 00:06:57,233
I got this.

122
00:06:57,300 --> 00:06:58,533
I won't let her get away.

123
00:07:04,900 --> 00:07:06,800
Oh, no. Son of a gun.

124
00:07:06,867 --> 00:07:07,967
I lost her again.

125
00:07:09,633 --> 00:07:11,267
I think that's her.

126
00:07:15,367 --> 00:07:16,367
Where are we heading, Ma'am?

127
00:07:17,567 --> 00:07:19,067
Oh, no. She's leaving.

128
00:07:19,900 --> 00:07:20,300
Hey!

129
00:07:23,633 --> 00:07:24,433
Sorry, Danilo.

130
00:07:24,900 --> 00:07:26,167
I couldn't catch her.

131
00:07:26,233 --> 00:07:27,800
She took a taxi.

132
00:07:27,867 --> 00:07:29,300
Okay.

133
00:07:29,367 --> 00:07:30,333
Thank you, Bukoy.

134
00:07:33,267 --> 00:07:34,900
What's going on, Dan?

135
00:07:34,967 --> 00:07:37,133
Can we still find Kayla?

136
00:07:39,367 --> 00:07:39,900
Wait.

137
00:07:40,567 --> 00:07:43,533
I know a traffic enforcer.

138
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:47,200
He can help us get in touch with
the Manila Traffic Authority.

139
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:48,867
So we can locate the taxi.

140
00:07:50,433 --> 00:07:51,167
Don't worry.

141
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:03,833
Flor, give us a minute.

142
00:08:04,633 --> 00:08:05,500
Okay, Ma'am.

143
00:08:25,967 --> 00:08:26,667
Mommy?

144
00:08:28,233 --> 00:08:30,067
Why? Is there a problem?

145
00:08:31,033 --> 00:08:33,400
Your test results are out.

146
00:08:38,500 --> 00:08:39,767
It's confirmed.

147
00:08:41,433 --> 00:08:44,500
You have an autoimmune
disease and leukemia.

148
00:08:46,933 --> 00:08:48,800
I wasn't surprised
with the findings

149
00:08:48,867 --> 00:08:51,233
because I know you're sick.

150
00:08:53,267 --> 00:08:55,267
But I guess this is the proof
you need to prove

151
00:08:55,367 --> 00:08:58,133
I'm telling the truth.

152
00:08:59,533 --> 00:09:00,367
No, Mommy.

153
00:09:02,133 --> 00:09:03,933
No, Mommy, this is not true.

154
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:06,033
This isn't true, Mommy.

155
00:09:06,100 --> 00:09:08,700
I can feel that I'm okay.

156
00:09:08,767 --> 00:09:10,500
That I'm not sick, Mommy.

157
00:09:13,800 --> 00:09:15,000
Mommy, promise.

158
00:09:15,067 --> 00:09:15,967
I'm feeling fine.

159
00:09:16,033 --> 00:09:17,533
I'm not sick.

160
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:19,033
Mookie, dear, calm down.

161
00:09:19,833 --> 00:09:20,500
Calm down.

162
00:09:21,267 --> 00:09:22,167
Just breathe.

163
00:09:23,100 --> 00:09:23,800
Just breathe.

164
00:09:24,933 --> 00:09:26,233
Breathe slowly.

165
00:09:26,300 --> 00:09:27,100
Calm down.

166
00:09:29,467 --> 00:09:31,567
Mookie, I know
you're disappointed.

167
00:09:33,867 --> 00:09:35,900
I know it's hard to accept.

168
00:09:37,667 --> 00:09:39,333
That's why I'm here for you.

169
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:43,367
I will take care of you, dear.

170
00:09:44,833 --> 00:09:46,767
I'm here for you.

171
00:09:47,733 --> 00:09:50,533
And I'll make sure
you'll get better.

172
00:09:51,933 --> 00:09:55,033
I'll do everything
to heal you, Mookie.

173
00:09:58,367 --> 00:10:01,833
I will find the best medicine,
so you'll get better faster.

174
00:10:03,167 --> 00:10:04,300
It's you and me.

175
00:10:05,033 --> 00:10:06,467
You and me forever.

176
00:10:08,133 --> 00:10:10,300
I'm the only one
you've got, Mookie.

177
00:10:12,367 --> 00:10:16,400
And I will do everything to
make you feel better.

178
00:10:16,467 --> 00:10:17,733
So, just trust me.

179
00:10:18,867 --> 00:10:21,667
Trust me the same way
that I trust you, Mookie.

180
00:10:23,500 --> 00:10:24,200
Okay?

181
00:10:25,100 --> 00:10:27,367
We will get through this
together, dear.

182
00:10:28,467 --> 00:10:30,733
We'll get through this.

183
00:10:32,533 --> 00:10:33,133
Okay?

184
00:10:40,433 --> 00:10:40,933
Here.

185
00:10:46,367 --> 00:10:47,033
Take this.

186
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:50,600
Take this.

187
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:54,700
Good girl.

188
00:11:01,500 --> 00:11:02,633
Open your mouth.

189
00:11:02,700 --> 00:11:04,333
I want to see
if you swallowed it.

190
00:11:05,733 --> 00:11:06,600
Good girl.

191
00:11:09,267 --> 00:11:10,033
Good girl.

192
00:11:11,233 --> 00:11:12,967
We'll get through
this, dear.

193
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:15,233
I will never leave you.

194
00:11:15,933 --> 00:11:16,400
Okay?

195
00:11:19,067 --> 00:11:20,867
I'm here for you, Mookie.

196
00:11:47,833 --> 00:11:49,867
There. That's her
taking the taxi.

197
00:11:52,700 --> 00:11:55,067
The next one is Silang Street.

198
00:11:56,433 --> 00:11:58,233
I hope we can trace the woman.

199
00:12:00,867 --> 00:12:02,000
It stopped.

200
00:12:16,433 --> 00:12:17,967
The driver has gotten off.

201
00:12:24,800 --> 00:12:26,500
He just went out to pee.

202
00:12:28,633 --> 00:12:31,833
We haven't installed any
CCTV at the corner

203
00:12:31,900 --> 00:12:33,300
where they turned.

204
00:12:33,367 --> 00:12:36,800
The Manila Traffic Authority
hasn't installed any CCTV yet.

205
00:12:37,567 --> 00:12:39,833
So, I'm sorry.

206
00:12:40,867 --> 00:12:42,600
Dead end again.

207
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:44,567
No, no.

208
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:47,633
I saw the plate number.

209
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:50,733
We can trace that driver.

210
00:13:11,967 --> 00:13:13,033
Hi, Zayn.

211
00:13:13,733 --> 00:13:15,867
Why do you look sad?

212
00:13:16,767 --> 00:13:19,133
I feel weak again, Zayn.

213
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:22,800
Mommy gave me medicines earlier.

214
00:13:23,667 --> 00:13:24,467
What?
Why?

215
00:13:26,533 --> 00:13:29,300
The results came out, Zayn.

216
00:13:31,200 --> 00:13:32,800
And it seems that...

217
00:13:33,967 --> 00:13:35,800
I have illnesses.

218
00:13:36,633 --> 00:13:37,667
Seems?

219
00:13:39,433 --> 00:13:40,933
You know, Zayn,

220
00:13:42,500 --> 00:13:44,800
I was convinced at first.

221
00:13:45,767 --> 00:13:47,867
I was about to accept it

222
00:13:47,933 --> 00:13:49,900
because that's what
the results were.

223
00:13:51,300 --> 00:13:55,467
And I really feel bad
that I doubted my mom.

224
00:13:57,700 --> 00:14:00,000
But I saw her face earlier...

225
00:14:01,567 --> 00:14:03,733
after giving me medicines.

226
00:14:12,400 --> 00:14:13,833
And I think, Zayn...

227
00:14:16,167 --> 00:14:16,800
I think...

228
00:14:17,733 --> 00:14:19,433
she faked the results.

229
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:25,633
I think what I'm going to ask
is already too much, but...

230
00:14:25,700 --> 00:14:26,467
No buts.

231
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:31,200
You can ask me any favor,
and I'll do it.

232
00:14:32,367 --> 00:14:35,200
I want to know the actual
results, Zayn.

233
00:14:36,167 --> 00:14:40,333
Results from the doctor,
not from my mom.

234
00:14:41,267 --> 00:14:43,300
Then I'll go and
get them for you.

235
00:14:43,367 --> 00:14:44,433
Thank you, Zayn.

236
00:14:45,500 --> 00:14:48,133
Hey, don't cry.

237
00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:49,733
You'll feel weaker.

238
00:14:50,533 --> 00:14:52,700
Get some rest, okay?

239
00:14:52,767 --> 00:14:54,233
Let's talk again tomorrow.

240
00:15:01,767 --> 00:15:03,200
You pointed a gun at them?

241
00:15:03,267 --> 00:15:04,300
Yes, Ma'am.

242
00:15:04,800 --> 00:15:07,367
And they seemed
to get scared.

243
00:15:07,867 --> 00:15:09,767
They both turned pale.

244
00:15:10,433 --> 00:15:11,633
They won't return.

245
00:15:11,700 --> 00:15:13,233
They can try and they'll
see what they'll get.

246
00:15:13,300 --> 00:15:14,333
How about Jade?

247
00:15:14,933 --> 00:15:16,867
She hasn't shown up, Ma'am.

248
00:15:18,767 --> 00:15:19,833
Okay.

249
00:15:19,900 --> 00:15:21,900
Thank you for the update, Ando.

250
00:15:53,733 --> 00:15:58,033
Zayn, I asked you to talk
to Dr. Villanueva.

251
00:15:58,100 --> 00:16:01,633
So we'll find out if the results
my mom gave me are real.

252
00:16:02,267 --> 00:16:03,733
She's in Hong Kong.

253
00:16:04,400 --> 00:16:06,833
And they didn't want
to give me her number.

254
00:16:06,900 --> 00:16:10,400
So, you just decided to steal
the results

255
00:16:10,500 --> 00:16:11,767
at the records station?

256
00:16:11,833 --> 00:16:12,600
Is that it?

257
00:16:12,667 --> 00:16:13,633
Yes.

258
00:16:14,333 --> 00:16:16,500
They won't just hand it to me.

259
00:16:16,567 --> 00:16:17,933
We're not related.

260
00:16:18,733 --> 00:16:21,033
Zayn, that's dangerous.

261
00:16:21,833 --> 00:16:23,133
Please.

262
00:16:23,200 --> 00:16:27,300
Let's just wait for
Dr. Villanueva's return.

263
00:16:27,767 --> 00:16:29,033
Mookie, come on.

264
00:16:29,100 --> 00:16:31,267
She has a two-week seminar
in Hong Kong.

265
00:16:31,333 --> 00:16:34,267
If you continue taking those
medicines for two weeks,

266
00:16:34,333 --> 00:16:36,700
you might go back
to your past condition.

267
00:16:36,767 --> 00:16:38,467
Do you want to be in
a wheelchair again?

268
00:16:39,467 --> 00:16:41,267
Trust me, okay?

269
00:16:41,367 --> 00:16:42,700
I won't get caught.

270
00:17:19,300 --> 00:17:20,633
Is my car okay now?

271
00:17:22,033 --> 00:17:23,400
Can I pick it up now?

272
00:17:24,567 --> 00:17:25,600
Okay, thank you.

273
00:17:26,933 --> 00:17:27,600
Olive.

274
00:17:27,667 --> 00:17:29,300
Jade's been calling me.

275
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:31,500
She said she'd been calling you
since last night,

276
00:17:31,567 --> 00:17:32,733
but you weren't picking up.

277
00:17:32,800 --> 00:17:33,633
Answer it.

278
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:39,667
She'll call again.

279
00:17:39,733 --> 00:17:41,033
Then don't answer.

280
00:17:41,900 --> 00:17:43,633
Anyway, I have to go.
I need to be somewhere.

281
00:17:43,700 --> 00:17:44,767
Take care of everything here.

282
00:17:44,833 --> 00:17:45,533
Where?
Where are you going?

283
00:17:47,233 --> 00:17:48,900
You don't have
an appointment today.

284
00:17:50,333 --> 00:17:53,200
Are you going to
Happy Paws Vet Aid Pharmacy?

285
00:17:54,267 --> 00:17:56,300
Are you going to purchase
Canixidol again?

286
00:17:58,267 --> 00:18:00,700
I know they have replenished
their stocks.

287
00:18:00,767 --> 00:18:02,500
They called yesterday
when you were away.

288
00:18:03,367 --> 00:18:07,267
So, are you going to get some to
inject into your daughter again?

289
00:18:07,333 --> 00:18:08,000
Yes.

290
00:18:08,633 --> 00:18:09,433
Satisfied?

291
00:18:10,533 --> 00:18:12,667
Why are you doing this again?

292
00:18:13,567 --> 00:18:15,967
So she can't escape anymore.

293
00:18:16,033 --> 00:18:18,667
My God, Olive!

294
00:18:18,733 --> 00:18:19,933
Please stop!

295
00:18:20,700 --> 00:18:22,467
Stop torturing your daughter.

296
00:18:22,567 --> 00:18:24,200
Have mercy on her.

297
00:18:24,867 --> 00:18:26,133
Please, Astrid.

298
00:18:27,167 --> 00:18:29,633
I'm not in the mood
to get mad right now.

299
00:18:29,700 --> 00:18:31,600
My head hurts.

300
00:18:31,667 --> 00:18:35,800
I hope, one day, Mookie
finds out she's not sick.

301
00:18:37,400 --> 00:18:40,633
That you just made
everything up.

302
00:19:00,433 --> 00:19:01,767
I'm getting in, Mooks.

303
00:19:03,367 --> 00:19:05,267
Zayn, please.

304
00:19:05,333 --> 00:19:06,733
Please be safe.

305
00:19:07,267 --> 00:19:09,300
I told you I won't get caught.

306
00:19:15,367 --> 00:19:18,467
Dra. Gonzales has been looking
for you, Jess.

307
00:19:18,533 --> 00:19:19,633
Bring her files to her.

308
00:19:19,700 --> 00:19:20,400
Hurry!

309
00:19:51,167 --> 00:19:51,900
QR.

310
00:20:07,733 --> 00:20:10,433
Mookie, I found
your test results!

311
00:20:13,033 --> 00:20:13,933
What does it say?

312
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:18,500
You're normal.

313
00:20:18,567 --> 00:20:20,100
You're not sick, Mookie.

314
00:20:26,667 --> 00:20:27,667
I'm not sick.

315
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:37,233
I'm not sick.

316
00:20:41,267 --> 00:20:42,467
I'm well.

317
00:20:43,567 --> 00:20:45,000
I'm well.

318
00:20:49,600 --> 00:20:50,267
I only have this.

319
00:20:51,800 --> 00:20:52,800
Again?

320
00:20:52,867 --> 00:20:54,000
Amazing!

321
00:20:54,067 --> 00:20:55,767
- Unbelievable.
- What can we do?

322
00:20:55,833 --> 00:20:58,233
You're on a roll, BFF!

323
00:20:58,300 --> 00:21:00,067
You've won three times in a row!

324
00:21:00,133 --> 00:21:02,367
- So lucky!
- Give us some of your winnings!

325
00:21:02,433 --> 00:21:02,933
Take a break first.

326
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:04,300
Buy some snacks.

327
00:21:04,367 --> 00:21:05,167
This is fresh.
Oh, wow!

328
00:21:06,067 --> 00:21:07,600
- There!
- I like that!

329
00:21:13,300 --> 00:21:15,000
Go get some, BFF.

330
00:21:19,200 --> 00:21:21,900
You're so lucky, Ligaya.

331
00:21:21,967 --> 00:21:23,933
You got the twin bananas.

332
00:21:24,667 --> 00:21:25,467
That's double luck.
Do you know that?

333
00:21:26,467 --> 00:21:27,933
But give it to someone else.

334
00:21:28,833 --> 00:21:29,800
No!

335
00:21:29,867 --> 00:21:31,967
I won't give my twins away!

336
00:21:32,033 --> 00:21:33,800
Why are you mad?

337
00:21:34,667 --> 00:21:36,333
Are you being stingy
with those bananas?

338
00:21:36,400 --> 00:21:37,000
Fool.

339
00:21:38,133 --> 00:21:39,800
Ligaya remembered something.

340
00:21:40,567 --> 00:21:41,467
Isko.

341
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:43,800
Isko, sorry.

342
00:21:43,867 --> 00:21:44,833
I'm sorry.

343
00:21:46,033 --> 00:21:47,233
I look like a fool, right?

344
00:21:48,167 --> 00:21:49,200
I'm sorry, I just...

345
00:21:50,400 --> 00:21:53,600
remembered my twins.

346
00:21:55,233 --> 00:21:58,967
I haven't seen them for almost
four decades now.

347
00:21:59,033 --> 00:22:00,033
I'm sorry.

348
00:22:06,200 --> 00:22:10,900
Bukoy, can we ask the hotel
so we don't have to wait here?

349
00:22:10,967 --> 00:22:15,333
We don't even know
the woman's name.

350
00:22:15,433 --> 00:22:18,867
We can ask for a copy
of the CCTV.

351
00:22:18,933 --> 00:22:20,633
I know what the woman
looks like, anyway.

352
00:22:20,700 --> 00:22:22,833
Don't you have any
pictures of her?

353
00:22:22,900 --> 00:22:25,233
So I'll know what the woman
who took my child looks like.

354
00:22:25,300 --> 00:22:26,700
I've been looking for it,

355
00:22:26,767 --> 00:22:29,067
but my wife said
she'd thrown it away.

356
00:22:30,700 --> 00:22:35,667
We have no choice but to wait.

357
00:22:37,433 --> 00:22:39,367
Isn't this too much for you,
Bukoy?

358
00:22:39,433 --> 00:22:41,033
We've taken too much
of your time.

359
00:22:41,100 --> 00:22:41,767
We're really sorry.

360
00:22:41,833 --> 00:22:42,833
No, it's okay.

361
00:22:42,900 --> 00:22:44,833
It's okay, Emma.
I also want to help.

362
00:22:45,367 --> 00:22:48,633
And I got restless

363
00:22:48,733 --> 00:22:52,067
when I heard you'd been thinking
Kayla was dead for 17 years.

364
00:22:52,133 --> 00:22:53,267
I'm also a father.

365
00:22:53,333 --> 00:22:55,033
Thank you.

366
00:22:55,100 --> 00:22:56,200
Thank you, Bukoy.

367
00:23:20,667 --> 00:23:22,967
Mookie, calm down.

368
00:23:23,067 --> 00:23:25,200
Maybe your mom
has an explanation

369
00:23:25,267 --> 00:23:27,067
- for why she did that.
- Flor, how can I calm down?

370
00:23:28,433 --> 00:23:30,833
What else does
she need to explain?

371
00:23:31,900 --> 00:23:32,967
She said she loved me.

372
00:23:33,033 --> 00:23:34,633
But why is she doing this to me?

373
00:23:34,700 --> 00:23:35,100
Why?

374
00:23:35,567 --> 00:23:36,600
Why?

375
00:23:37,567 --> 00:23:39,200
I don't understand, Flor.

376
00:24:09,900 --> 00:24:10,900
Hi!

377
00:24:13,633 --> 00:24:14,367
Liar!

378
00:24:15,533 --> 00:24:16,433
You're a iar!

379
00:24:18,033 --> 00:24:20,333
Why did you lie to me, Mommy?

380
00:24:31,933 --> 00:24:32,700
Bukoy.

381
00:24:32,767 --> 00:24:34,733
Some women are going out.

382
00:24:34,800 --> 00:24:35,533
Can you check?

383
00:24:38,167 --> 00:24:40,600
The woman isn't one of them.

384
00:24:42,667 --> 00:24:43,667
I'm sorry, Emma.

385
00:24:43,733 --> 00:24:44,300
I'll just use the restroom.

386
00:24:44,367 --> 00:24:45,333
I need to pee.

387
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:46,000
Okay.

388
00:24:46,067 --> 00:24:47,467
Me, too. I need to pee.

389
00:24:47,533 --> 00:24:48,867
Let Bukoy go first.
So he can come back quick.

390
00:24:48,933 --> 00:24:50,200
Okay, I will.

391
00:24:50,267 --> 00:24:51,033
Okay.

392
00:24:54,033 --> 00:24:54,800
Olive?

393
00:24:55,633 --> 00:24:56,167
Olive!
Olive!

394
00:24:58,200 --> 00:24:58,900
Olive!

395
00:24:59,500 --> 00:25:00,267
Olive!

396
00:25:03,967 --> 00:25:05,367
What are you doing here?

397
00:25:05,433 --> 00:25:07,100
How about you?
What are you doing here?

398
00:25:08,033 --> 00:25:09,600
How's Mookie?

399
00:25:10,567 --> 00:25:11,767
She's fine.

400
00:25:11,833 --> 00:25:12,967
Happy.

401
00:25:13,033 --> 00:25:14,333
Is she able to walk now?

402
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:17,867
I believe that's none
of your business, Emma.

403
00:25:31,167 --> 00:25:33,433
Why did you lie to me, Mommy?

404
00:25:34,633 --> 00:25:35,300
Me?

405
00:25:36,133 --> 00:25:37,100
Lied?

406
00:25:38,967 --> 00:25:40,333
Mommy?

407
00:25:41,067 --> 00:25:41,600
Wait.

408
00:25:42,233 --> 00:25:44,500
Are you Maria Angela?

409
00:25:44,567 --> 00:25:46,133
What trickery is this?

410
00:25:47,400 --> 00:25:50,633
It's you!

411
00:25:50,700 --> 00:25:54,633
Nice to meet you, Maria Angela!

412
00:25:56,233 --> 00:25:58,033
Wait, what's going on?

413
00:25:58,900 --> 00:26:00,567
What is it this time, Mommy?

414
00:26:10,033 --> 00:26:13,067
What the hell are you doing
in my house, Jade?

415
00:26:13,833 --> 00:26:15,067
Olive!

416
00:26:26,533 --> 00:26:29,133
Munchausen Syndrome by Proxy?

417
00:26:29,200 --> 00:26:29,667
What is it?

418
00:26:29,733 --> 00:26:30,867
What's Munchau?

419
00:26:30,933 --> 00:26:32,800
It's a psychological disorder.

420
00:26:32,867 --> 00:26:34,600
Mothers are often
affected by it.

421
00:26:34,667 --> 00:26:37,467
And they give their
children illnesses.

422
00:26:37,533 --> 00:26:39,600
I won't sell
the ancestral house

423
00:26:39,667 --> 00:26:41,767
If that's the case, then...

424
00:26:42,567 --> 00:26:44,167
I'll stay in your house.

425
00:26:46,133 --> 00:26:46,867
What is...

426
00:26:46,933 --> 00:26:47,967
Mookie?

427
00:26:48,033 --> 00:26:50,967
I know you're faking
my test results!

428
00:26:51,033 --> 00:26:53,733
And the Canixidol you're
injecting me

429
00:26:53,800 --> 00:26:55,367
is for animals, right?

430
00:26:55,433 --> 00:26:58,533
You are making me sick!
